\title{Phyllotaxis}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{trit}{1}

\meta{description}{Succulent rosette growth as propagator network — golden angle = Nash equilibrium, auxin chemotaxis = affective taxis, BCI modulation = closed-loop biofeedback}

\subtree{
\title{Phyllotaxis}
\blockquote{Spiral leaf arrangement as a propagator network where the golden angle emerges as Nash equilibrium.}

\p{\strong{Trit}: +1 (PLUS - Generator) \strong{Color}: #3DD98F (green — growth)}

\subtree{
\title{Core Insight}
\p{The Douady-Couder model of phyllotaxis IS a propagator network (SDF Ch7):}

\ul{
\li{\strong{Cells} = primordia (partial information: position, auxin, inhibition)}
\li{\strong{Propagators} = Gaussian inhibition kernels (constraint transformers)}
\li{\strong{Scheduler} = plastochron clock (SICP Ch5 explicit control)}
\li{\strong{Quiescence} = golden angle spiral (Nash equilibrium)}
}

\p{The golden angle (137.508°) is not designed — it EMERGES from the constraint network, just as Nash equilibria emerge from propagator-based game solving.}
}

